      "patch": "@@ -752,7 +752,7 @@¥n {¥"id¥":¥"bd-wzud¥",¥"title¥":¥"Add locale ABI fuzz target for category and C-locale semantics¥",¥"status¥":¥"closed¥",¥"priority¥":2,¥"issue_type¥":¥"task¥",¥"assignee¥":¥"ubuntu¥",¥"created_at¥":¥"2026-04-16T22:45:10.151703054Z¥",¥"created_by¥":¥"ubuntu¥",¥"updated_at¥":¥"2026-04-16T22:57:02.419729573Z¥",¥"closed_at¥":¥"2026-04-16T22:57:02.417481666Z¥",¥"close_reason¥":¥"Added locale ABI fuzz target, architecture metadata, regenerated conformance artifact, and verified with rch workspace gates.¥",¥"source_repo¥":¥".¥",¥"compaction_level¥":0,¥"original_size¥":0}¥n {¥"id¥": ¥"bd-x2sq¥", ¥"title¥": ¥"bd-1rf subtask: NSS strict+hardened fixture/e2e closure with matrix drift checks¥", ¥"description¥": ¥"Background:¥¥n- NSS backend completion must be reflected in conformance/e2e gates and support matrix truth.¥¥n¥¥nGoal:¥¥n- Build strict/hardened NSS fixture pack and close evidence loop for supported files backend APIs.¥¥n¥¥nDeliverables:¥¥n1) Fixture sets for passwd/group/hosts lookups.¥¥n2) E2E scenarios using integration binaries.¥¥n3) Support matrix and reality report consistency updates.¥¥n¥¥nAcceptance Criteria:¥¥n- NSS fixture/e2e suite passes deterministically in target scope.¥¥n- Docs/matrix/report remain drift-free under guard scripts.¥¥n¥¥nVerification & Logging:¥¥n- E2E scripts with comprehensive structured logs and artifact refs.¥", ¥"acceptance_criteria¥": ¥"## Acceptance Criteria¥¥nImplementation must preserve all existing functionality and claims while adding deterministic verification coverage.¥¥n¥¥n### Mandatory Verification Gate¥¥n- Comprehensive unit tests are required for all touched logic: positive, negative, adversarial, and regression.¥¥n- Deterministic e2e scripts are required for all externally visible behavior in strict and hardened mode where relevant.¥¥n- Structured logs are mandatory for unit/e2e runs with fields: `trace_id`, `mode`, `api_family`, `symbol`, `decision_path`, `healing_action`, `errno`, `latency_ns`, `artifact_refs`.¥¥n- Closure evidence must include exact test commands, expected outputs/thresholds, and representative failure signatures.¥¥n- CI must persist logs, diffs, and reports with deterministic naming and retention for replay/triage.¥¥n- Tooling contract: deterministic orchestration/traceability uses `/dp/asupersync`, and deterministic diff/snapshot/TUI evidence uses `/dp/frankentui`.¥", ¥"notes¥": ¥"2026-02-18 status (IcyCat): NSS fixture executor wiring completed in crates/frankenlibc_conformance/src/lib.rs; NSS fixture packs expanded (pwd_ops/grp_ops/resolver); new integration fixture tests/integration/fixture_nss.c added and c_fixture_spec/link_test updated. Verification: cargo fmt --check PASS; rch cargo check/clippy PASS; rch cargo test -p frankenlibc_conformance PASS (57 tests); rch bash scripts/check_c_fixture_suite.sh PASS. Blockers: workspace test hang in frankenlibc-core pthread::thread::tests::child_thread_can_write_shared_memory (tracked as bd-2o7i); global drift/maintenance gates failing due current repository-wide state; c_fixture_suite currently failing broadly and fixture_nss times out under preload though it passes without preload.¥", ¥"status¥": ¥"closed¥", ¥"priority¥": 2, ¥"issue_type¥": ¥"task¥", ¥"assignee¥": ¥"IcyCat¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-02-12T15:01:54.194463803Z¥", ¥"created_by¥": ¥"ubuntu¥", ¥"updated_at¥": ¥"2026-04-13T23:51:55.211602975Z¥", ¥"closed_at¥": ¥"2026-04-13T23:51:55.211280986Z¥", ¥"close_reason¥": ¥"done¥", ¥"source_repo¥": ¥".¥", ¥"compaction_level¥": 0, ¥"original_size¥": 0, ¥"labels¥": [¥"critique¥", ¥"e2e¥", ¥"nss¥", ¥"testing¥", ¥"verification¥"], ¥"dependencies¥": [{¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-x2sq¥", ¥"depends_on_id¥": ¥"bd-2yhf¥", ¥"type¥": ¥"blocks¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-02-26T06:17:34Z¥", ¥"created_by¥": ¥"import¥", ¥"metadata¥": ¥"{}¥", ¥"thread_id¥": ¥"¥"}, {¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-x2sq¥", ¥"depends_on_id¥": ¥"bd-3ehb¥", ¥"type¥": ¥"blocks¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-02-26T06:17:34Z¥", ¥"created_by¥": ¥"import¥", ¥"metadata¥": ¥"{}¥", ¥"thread_id¥": ¥"¥"}, {¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-x2sq¥", ¥"depends_on_id¥": ¥"bd-3rag¥", ¥"type¥": ¥"blocks¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-02-26T06:17:34Z¥", ¥"created_by¥": ¥"import¥", ¥"metadata¥": ¥"{}¥", ¥"thread_id¥": ¥"¥"}, {¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-x2sq¥", ¥"depends_on_id¥": ¥"bd-3vtx¥", ¥"type¥": ¥"blocks¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-02-26T06:17:34Z¥", ¥"created_by¥": ¥"import¥", ¥"metadata¥": ¥"{}¥", ¥"thread_id¥": ¥"¥"}]}¥n {¥"id¥":¥"bd-x63h¥",¥"title¥":¥"Execute stdlib_numeric fixture through isolated harness¥",¥"description¥":¥"Upgrade stdlib_numeric conformance from schema-only validation to per-case isolated harness execution, plus top-level fixture metadata assertions.¥",¥"status¥":¥"closed¥",¥"priority¥":2,¥"issue_type¥":¥"task¥",¥"assignee¥":¥"ubuntu¥",¥"created_at¥":¥"2026-04-16T23:52:21.427261418Z¥",¥"created_by¥":¥"ubuntu¥",¥"updated_at¥":¥"2026-04-16T23:55:21.122508633Z¥",¥"closed_at¥":¥"2026-04-16T23:55:21.120418924Z¥",¥"close_reason¥":¥"Upgraded stdlib_numeric conformance coverage to execute each fixture case through the isolated harness subprocess path and added fixture metadata assertions.¥",¥"source_repo¥":¥".¥",¥"compaction_level¥":0,¥"original_size¥":0}¥n-{¥"id¥":¥"bd-x7jd¥",¥"title¥":¥"POSIX/hosts(5) conformance table for /etc/hosts parser¥",¥"description¥":¥"frankenlibc-core::resolv has unit tests for parse_hosts_line/lookup_hosts but no spec-annotated conformance table. Add Pattern-4 spec-derived table with cases citing hosts(5) + RFC 952 + RFC 1123 (hostname validation). Coverage: whitespace (spaces/tabs/mixed), case insensitivity, IPv4/IPv6 mix, multi-alias lines, comments (start/mid-line), blank lines, CRLF, malformed addresses, RFC 952/1123 hostname char set. Scope: crates/frankenlibc-core/src/resolv/mod.rs #[cfg(test)] module. One commit per section group.¥",¥"status¥":¥"in_progress¥",¥"priority¥":2,¥"issue_type¥":¥"task¥",¥"created_at¥":¥"2026-04-20T19:25:33.676462834Z¥",¥"created_by¥":¥"ubuntu¥",¥"updated_at¥":¥"2026-04-20T19:25:39.145684949Z¥",¥"source_repo¥":¥".¥",¥"compaction_level¥":0,¥"original_size¥":0}¥n+{¥"id¥":¥"bd-x7jd¥",¥"title¥":¥"POSIX/hosts(5) conformance table for /etc/hosts parser¥",¥"description¥":¥"frankenlibc-core::resolv has unit tests for parse_hosts_line/lookup_hosts but no spec-annotated conformance table. Add Pattern-4 spec-derived table with cases citing hosts(5) + RFC 952 + RFC 1123 (hostname validation). Coverage: whitespace (spaces/tabs/mixed), case insensitivity, IPv4/IPv6 mix, multi-alias lines, comments (start/mid-line), blank lines, CRLF, malformed addresses, RFC 952/1123 hostname char set. Scope: crates/frankenlibc-core/src/resolv/mod.rs #[cfg(test)] module. One commit per section group.¥",¥"status¥":¥"closed¥",¥"priority¥":2,¥"issue_type¥":¥"task¥",¥"created_at¥":¥"2026-04-20T19:25:33.676462834Z¥",¥"created_by¥":¥"ubuntu¥",¥"updated_at¥":¥"2026-04-20T19:29:43.474768096Z¥",¥"closed_at¥":¥"2026-04-20T19:29:43.472712968Z¥",¥"close_reason¥":¥"Added 3 POSIX/resolver(5)/hosts(5) spec-derived conformance tables across 2 commits: ad881c2 (hosts parse 16 cases + lookup 7 cases), 0b464ba (resolv.conf 12 cases). Total 35 cases with spec_ref citations for hosts(5), RFC 952, RFC 1123, RFC 1035, resolver(5), and <resolv.h> MAXNS cap.¥",¥"source_repo¥":¥".¥",¥"compaction_level¥":0,¥"original_size¥":0}¥n {¥"id¥": ¥"bd-xxd9¥", ¥"title¥": ¥"bd-25n subtask: Threading/futex lifecycle exhaustive unit+stress test packs¥", ¥"description¥": ¥"Background:¥¥n- Threading and synchronization logic remains a critical defect surface.¥¥n¥¥nGoal:¥¥n- Build exhaustive unit test packs for pthread/futex/thread bootstrap lifecycle semantics.¥¥n¥¥nDeliverables:¥¥n1) Mutex/condvar/thread/join/detach API-level unit tests.¥¥n2) Concurrency adversarial tests with deterministic scheduling controls where feasible.¥¥n3) Regression suite for known deadlock/hang signatures.¥¥n¥¥nAcceptance Criteria:¥¥n- Threading test packs cover success, misuse, contention, timeout, teardown paths.¥¥n- Regression signatures are pinned and automatically checked.¥¥n¥¥nVerification & Logging:¥¥n- Unit and stress test scripts.¥¥n- Structured logs with thread/event timelines and failure markers.¥", ¥"status¥": ¥"closed¥", ¥"priority¥": 0, ¥"issue_type¥": ¥"task¥", ¥"assignee¥": ¥"DustyRiver¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-02-12T15:02:38.991066758Z¥", ¥"created_by¥": ¥"ubuntu¥", ¥"updated_at¥": ¥"2026-02-16T14:34:54.992244359Z¥", ¥"closed_at¥": ¥"2026-02-16T14:34:54.992224261Z¥", ¥"close_reason¥": ¥"Thread/futex lifecycle pack now includes mutex/condvar/rwlock/once/tsd + lifecycle regressions (including self-join). Validated via targeted rch test binaries and workspace quality gates.¥", ¥"source_repo¥": ¥".¥", ¥"compaction_level¥": 0, ¥"original_size¥": 0, ¥"labels¥": [¥"critique¥", ¥"pthread¥", ¥"testing¥", ¥"unit¥", ¥"verification¥"], ¥"comments¥": [{¥"id¥": 1217, ¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-xxd9¥", ¥"author¥": ¥"DustyRiver¥", ¥"text¥": ¥"Taking ownership of `bd-xxd9` based on `bv` robot triage.¥¥n¥¥nTriage evidence (robot mode):¥¥n- `bv --robot-next` top pick surfaced `bd-rqn` (already in progress).¥¥n- `bv --robot-triage` critical path shows `bd-25n` as top impact node, blocked by `bd-xxd9`.¥¥n- `bd-25n` currently unblocks 10 downstream issues, so advancing `bd-xxd9` is highest-impact actionable unblock.¥¥n¥¥nExecution start:¥¥n- Reassigned `bd-xxd9` to `DustyRiver` and keeping status `in_progress`.¥¥n- Starting with release-mode pthread regression signatures already reproduced under LD_PRELOAD:¥¥n  - `python3_print` timeout¥¥n  - `coreutils_ls_tmp` segfault¥¥n  - `sort/wc/redis` timeouts¥¥n- Will add deterministic unit+stress coverage and structured artifact references as evidence.¥¥n¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-02-16T06:19:58Z¥"}, {¥"id¥": 1218, ¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-xxd9¥", ¥"author¥": ¥"Dicklesworthstone¥", ¥"text¥": ¥"Progress update for `bd-xxd9` (threading/futex lifecycle unit+stress packs):¥¥n¥¥nImplemented in `crates/frankenlibc-abi/tests/pthread_thread_lifecycle_test.rs`:¥¥n- Added deterministic stress harness helpers (`env_usize`, `run_create_join_roundtrip_iters`, `run_detach_join_esrch_iters`).¥¥n- Converted lifecycle stress tests to bounded defaults to prevent CI hangs:¥¥n  - `pthread_create_join_roundtrip_stress` now uses `FRANKENLIBC_THREAD_ROUNDTRIP_STRESS_ITERS` (default `16`, cap `128`).¥¥n  - `pthread_create_join_parallel_batch_stress` now uses `FRANKENLIBC_THREAD_PARALLEL_BATCH` (default `8`, cap `32`).¥¥n  - `pthread_detach_join_esrch_stress` now uses `FRANKENLIBC_THREAD_DETACH_STRESS_ITERS` (default `16`, cap `128`).¥¥n- Added explicit opt-in endurance tests (ignored by default):¥¥n  - `pthread_create_join_roundtrip_long_stress_profile`¥¥n  - `pthread_detach_join_esrch_long_stress_profile`¥¥n¥¥nValidation run (CPU-intensive cargo via `rch`):¥¥n- `rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target-dustyriver cargo test -p frankenlibc-abi --test pthread_thread_lifecycle_test -- --nocapture` ¥¥u2705 (`8 passed, 2 ignored`)¥¥n- `rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target-dustyriver cargo test -p frankenlibc-abi --test pthread_cond_core_test -- --nocapture` ¥¥u2705 (`6 passed`)¥¥n- `rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target-dustyriver cargo fmt --check` ¥¥u2705¥¥n- `rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target-dustyriver cargo check --workspace --all-targets` ¥¥u2705¥¥n- `rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target-dustyriver cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings` ¥¥u2705¥¥n¥¥nNotes:¥¥n- `rch` remote daemon intermittently timed out in this environment; fail-open local execution was used where needed (per AGENTS.md behavior).¥¥n- `bd-xxd9` remains `in_progress`; next step is extending regression signatures toward known LD_PRELOAD deadlock/timeout patterns while preserving deterministic runtimes.¥¥n¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-02-16T06:43:30Z¥"}, {¥"id¥": 1219, ¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-xxd9¥", ¥"author¥": ¥"Dicklesworthstone¥", ¥"text¥": ¥"Additional `bd-xxd9` progress update:¥¥n¥¥nWhat I advanced in this pass:¥¥n- Added ABI-level condvar timedwait argument-validation regression in `crates/frankenlibc-abi/tests/pthread_cond_core_test.rs`:¥¥n  - `condvar_timedwait_rejects_null_abstime_and_invalid_nsec`¥¥n- Added lifecycle handle-consumption misuse regression in `crates/frankenlibc-abi/tests/pthread_thread_lifecycle_test.rs`:¥¥n  - `pthread_join_then_reuse_handle_is_esrch`¥¥n¥¥nStability hardening for lifecycle stress coverage:¥¥n- Converted default stress entries to explicit opt-in (`#[ignore]`) with clear labels to avoid wedging default test runs under known native-threading flake windows:¥¥n  - `pthread_create_join_roundtrip_stress`¥¥n  - `pthread_create_join_parallel_batch_stress`¥¥n  - `pthread_detach_join_esrch_stress`¥¥n- Long-run stress variants remain ignored and available for explicit endurance runs.¥¥n¥¥nNew discovered defect (tracked separately):¥¥n- Created child bug bead `bd-xxd9.1`:¥¥n  - ¥¥¥"Native pthread self-join can deadlock under thread lifecycle path¥¥¥"¥¥n  - Repro came from a self-join regression attempt that could wedge the lifecycle suite.¥¥n¥¥nValidation (via `rch exec -- ...`):¥¥n- `cargo test -p frankenlibc-abi --test pthread_thread_lifecycle_test -- --nocapture` ¥¥u2705 (`6 passed, 5 ignored`)¥¥n- `cargo test -p frankenlibc-abi --test pthread_cond_core_test -- --nocapture` ¥¥u2705 (`7 passed`)¥¥n- `cargo fmt --check` ¥¥u2705¥¥n- `cargo check --workspace --all-targets` ¥¥u2705 (remote build succeeded; artifact retrieval path was flaky)¥¥n- `cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings` ¥¥u2705 (remote build succeeded; artifact retrieval path was flaky)¥¥n¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-02-16T07:05:11Z¥"}, {¥"id¥": 1220, ¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-xxd9¥", ¥"author¥": ¥"Dicklesworthstone¥", ¥"text¥": ¥"Subtask progress: advanced  self-join deadlock hardening with code changes in core thread lifecycle + ABI join guard and validated lifecycle/condvar suites.  remains in_progress while we finish deterministic self-join coverage so regression can be unignored safely.¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-02-16T14:07:12Z¥"}, {¥"id¥": 1221, ¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-xxd9¥", ¥"author¥": ¥"Dicklesworthstone¥", ¥"text¥": ¥"Subtask progress: advanced `bd-xxd9.1` self-join deadlock hardening with core lifecycle + ABI join-entry guards and re-validated lifecycle/condvar suites.¥¥n¥¥nCurrent state:¥¥n- Parent `bd-xxd9` remains in progress.¥¥n- Child bug `bd-xxd9.1` remains in progress while we finish deterministic startup-window handling needed to unignore the self-join regression probe.¥¥n¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-02-16T14:08:28Z¥"}, {¥"id¥": 1222, ¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-xxd9¥", ¥"author¥": ¥"Dicklesworthstone¥", ¥"text¥": ¥"Progress update:¥¥n- Closed child bug `bd-xxd9.1` after re-enabling `pthread_self_join_is_rejected_with_edeadlk` in default lifecycle suite.¥¥n- Validation evidence:¥¥n  - repeated explicit runs of self-join probe (`--ignored`) passed 3/3 via `rch`¥¥n  - default lifecycle suite now includes self-join test and passed: `7 passed, 5 ignored`¥¥n  - condvar suite passed: `7 passed`¥¥n  - workspace gates passed: `cargo fmt --check`, `cargo check --workspace --all-targets`, `cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings`¥¥n¥¥n`bd-xxd9` remains in-progress for broader threading/futex lifecycle pack completion beyond this self-join defect.¥¥n¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-02-16T14:31:41Z¥"}]}¥n {¥"id¥": ¥"bd-xxd9.1¥", ¥"title¥": ¥"Native pthread self-join can deadlock under thread lifecycle path¥", ¥"description¥": ¥"Observed while developing bd-xxd9 regression tests: a child thread invoking pthread_join on its own pthread_t can hang indefinitely instead of returning EDEADLK. Repro path came from an ABI test that passed self handle via shared slot and called pthread_join(self). This can wedge the lifecycle suite (global test guard then blocks subsequent tests). Need root-cause fix in native join/create lifecycle path plus deterministic non-hanging regression.¥", ¥"status¥": ¥"closed¥", ¥"priority¥": 1, ¥"issue_type¥": ¥"bug¥", ¥"assignee¥": ¥"DustyRiver¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-02-16T07:04:33.822441437Z¥", ¥"created_by¥": ¥"DustyRiver¥", ¥"updated_at¥": ¥"2026-02-16T14:31:41.100312883Z¥", ¥"closed_at¥": ¥"2026-02-16T14:31:41.100295009Z¥", ¥"close_reason¥": ¥"Self-join deadlock hardened: core+ABI guards in place; regression test re-enabled in default lifecycle suite and validated via repeated rch runs + workspace gates.¥", ¥"source_repo¥": ¥".¥", ¥"compaction_level¥": 0, ¥"original_size¥": 0, ¥"labels¥": [¥"pthread¥", ¥"regression¥", ¥"threading¥"], ¥"dependencies¥": [{¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-xxd9.1¥", ¥"depends_on_id¥": ¥"bd-xxd9¥", ¥"type¥": ¥"parent-child¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-02-26T06:17:34Z¥", ¥"created_by¥": ¥"import¥", ¥"metadata¥": ¥"{}¥", ¥"thread_id¥": ¥"¥"}], ¥"comments¥": [{¥"id¥": 1223, ¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-xxd9.1¥", ¥"author¥": ¥"Dicklesworthstone¥", ¥"text¥": ¥"`bd-xxd9.1` investigation update (self-join deadlock):¥¥n¥¥nRepro status:¥¥n- Repro remains valid: explicit self-join regression (`pthread_self_join_is_rejected_with_edeadlk`) can hang >60s when run standalone.¥¥n- This is why the self-join regression remains excluded from default suite (no default CI wedging).¥¥n¥¥nWhat I tested:¥¥n1. Parent-side `tid` publication in `create_thread` (store returned child tid before startup wait).¥¥n2. Child-side early `tid` publication in trampoline.¥¥n3. Removed `std::thread::yield_now()` from helper (to avoid clone/TLS interaction suspicion) in explicit repro path.¥¥n¥¥nOutcome:¥¥n- None of the above alone eliminated the explicit self-join hang in this environment.¥¥n- Default lifecycle suite remains stable with stress tests opt-in/ignored.¥¥n¥¥nCurrent safe posture:¥¥n- Keep self-join issue tracked as `bd-xxd9.1` (in_progress).¥¥n- Keep non-hanging lifecycle/condvar regressions active in default runs.¥¥n- Keep stress/endurance paths opt-in (`#[ignore]`) until self-join path is resolved.¥¥n¥¥nValidation re-confirmed during this pass:¥¥n- `cargo test -p frankenlibc-abi --test pthread_thread_lifecycle_test -- --nocapture` ¥¥u2705 (`6 passed, 5 ignored`)¥¥n- `cargo test -p frankenlibc-abi --test pthread_cond_core_test -- --nocapture` ¥¥u2705 (`7 passed`)¥¥n- `cargo fmt --check` ¥¥u2705¥¥n- `cargo check --workspace --all-targets` ¥¥u2705¥¥n- `cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings` ¥¥u2705¥¥n  (all run through `rch exec -- ...`; artifact retrieval warnings from worker are environmental and occurred after successful remote command exit)¥¥n¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-02-16T07:24:14Z¥"}, {¥"id¥": 1224, ¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-xxd9.1¥", ¥"author¥": ¥"Dicklesworthstone¥", ¥"text¥": ¥"Progress update (self-join hardening pass):¥¥n¥¥nImplemented:¥¥n- `crates/frankenlibc-core/src/pthread/thread.rs`: added `ThreadHandle.self_tid` (stable child-captured identity), early publication of child tid/self_tid in trampoline, and an additional running-state self-join guard in `join_thread` before futex wait paths.¥¥n- `crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/pthread_abi.rs`: added ABI-level early self-join rejection in `native_pthread_join`:¥¥n  - direct `thread == my_tid` guard for fallback raw-TID self IDs¥¥n  - registry-backed check against target handle `tid/self_tid` while `THREAD_STARTING|THREAD_RUNNING` before handle removal/core join call.¥¥n- `crates/frankenlibc-abi/tests/pthread_thread_lifecycle_test.rs`: kept `pthread_self_join_is_rejected_with_edeadlk` as explicit opt-in (`#[ignore]`) due remaining scheduler-sensitive startup window during this bead; avoids default-suite wedge while hardening continues.¥¥n¥¥nValidation (using rch for cargo test/check/clippy):¥¥n- `cargo test -p frankenlibc-abi --test pthread_thread_lifecycle_test -- --nocapture` ¥¥u2705 (`6 passed, 6 ignored`)¥¥n- `cargo test -p frankenlibc-abi --test pthread_cond_core_test -- --nocapture` ¥¥u2705 (`7 passed`)¥¥n- `cargo check --workspace --all-targets` ¥¥u2705¥¥n- `cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings` ¥¥u2705¥¥n- `cargo fmt --check` ¥¥u2705¥¥n¥¥nStatus:¥¥n- Deadlock incidence reduced in explicit probes, but startup-order nondeterminism still appears in repeated forced self-join probes; keeping this bug in-progress for another pass to make self-join assertion fully deterministic and unignore regression.¥¥n¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-02-16T14:08:24Z¥"}, {¥"id¥": 1225, ¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-xxd9.1¥", ¥"author¥": ¥"Dicklesworthstone¥", ¥"text¥": ¥"New execution slice started from `bv --robot-triage`:¥¥n¥¥n- `bd-25n` remains highest-impact node but blocked by `bd-xxd9`.¥¥n- `bd-xxd9.1` remains the active blocker bug in this lane.¥¥n¥¥nThis slice focus:¥¥n1) Remove startup-order nondeterminism in self-join path (`pthread_join(pthread_self())`).¥¥n2) Drive deterministic behavior toward strict `EDEADLK` in explicit probe runs.¥¥n3) If stable, unignore `pthread_self_join_is_rejected_with_edeadlk`; otherwise keep it explicit opt-in with updated evidence.¥¥n¥¥nStarting implementation now in:¥¥n- `crates/frankenlibc-core/src/pthread/thread.rs`¥¥n- `crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/pthread_abi.rs`¥¥n- `crates/frankenlibc-abi/tests/pthread_thread_lifecycle_test.rs`¥¥n¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-02-16T14:28:33Z¥"}]}¥n {¥"id¥": ¥"bd-xxyb¥", ¥"title¥": ¥"Investigate Python startup perf regression in LD_PRELOAD smoke suite (51/7/6)¥", ¥"description¥": ¥"## Problem¥¥nLD_PRELOAD smoke suite regressed from 58/0/6 to 51/7/6. All 7 failures are Python-related with failure_signature=startup_perf_regression. Correctness is fine (parity_pass=true) ¥¥u2014 only startup latency exceeds the perf gate threshold.¥¥n¥¥n## Failing Cases¥¥n- strict: python3_print, stress_python_{1..5}¥¥n- hardened: stress_python_5¥¥n¥¥n## Probable Cause¥¥nRecent changes to signal handling and malloc that added overhead:¥¥n1. signal_abi.rs: Signal trampoline installation, SA_RESTORER marshalling, deferred delivery critical sections¥¥n2. malloc_abi.rs: Signal critical section entry/exit around every malloc/calloc/free/realloc call¥¥n3. host_resolve.rs: Streaming /proc/self/maps parser changes¥¥n¥¥nPython startup is particularly sensitive because it calls sigaction dozens of times during interpreter init, and does heavy allocation.¥¥n¥¥n## Investigation Steps¥¥n1. Profile Python startup under LD_PRELOAD to identify the hotspot¥¥n2. Check if the malloc signal critical section is the bottleneck (atomic ops on every alloc)¥¥n3. Check if sigaction trampoline installation overhead is significant¥¥n4. Consider: make signal critical sections opt-in (only when FRANKENLIBC_MODE=hardened)¥¥n¥¥n## Acceptance Criteria¥¥nSmoke suite returns to 58/0/6 (or 57/0/7 with the new skipped binary). Python startup perf within threshold.¥", ¥"status¥": ¥"closed¥", ¥"priority¥": 2, ¥"issue_type¥": ¥"bug¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-04-03T18:43:55.100768393Z¥", ¥"created_by¥": ¥"ubuntu¥", ¥"updated_at¥": ¥"2026-04-04T00:24:27.961421919Z¥", ¥"closed_at¥": ¥"2026-04-04T00:23:57.951709506Z¥", ¥"close_reason¥": ¥"Smoke gate back to 58/0/6; strict+hardened Python cases green¥", ¥"source_repo¥": ¥".¥", ¥"compaction_level¥": 0, ¥"original_size¥": 0, ¥"labels¥": [¥"malloc¥", ¥"performance¥", ¥"regression¥", ¥"signal¥"], ¥"comments¥": [{¥"id¥": 1367, ¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-xxyb¥", ¥"author¥": ¥"ubuntu¥", ¥"text¥": ¥"Investigation finding: strace -c output is garbled under LD_PRELOAD because our printf engine does NOT support POSIX positional format specifiers (%n$s, %n$d). strace uses these extensively for column-aligned output. This is a separate correctness bug from the perf regression. The perf regression itself appears to be from the 275ms Python startup (vs 15ms native) ¥¥u2014 likely caused by signal trampoline overhead per sigaction call (67 calls) and /proc/self/maps reads (6 reads). The positional printf bug should be a separate bead.¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-04-03T18:46:53Z¥"}, {¥"id¥": 1368, ¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-xxyb¥", ¥"author¥": ¥"ubuntu¥", ¥"text¥": ¥"Root cause analysis: The 275ms Python startup (vs 15ms native) is primarily from host symbol resolution overhead during early bootstrap, not from the signal trampoline per se. Each of the 67 sigaction calls triggers runtime_policy::decide() + kernel struct marshalling + trampoline installation, but the main cost is likely the resolve_host_symbol_raw calls reading /proc/self/maps (6 reads confirmed via strace). The signal trampoline itself is cheap after first install. Possible fixes: (1) cache /proc/self/maps content, (2) lazy-resolve symbols on first actual use not on every sigaction, (3) batch symbol resolution at startup. This is an optimization task, not a correctness bug.¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-04-03T18:47:54Z¥"}, {¥"id¥": 1374, ¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-xxyb¥", ¥"author¥": ¥"LavenderMarsh¥", ¥"text¥": ¥"First perf datapoint after strict allocator fast-path reorder in malloc_abi.rs: rebuilt release lib via rch (cargo build -p frankenlibc-abi --release) and remeasured local python3 -c print(1) startup over 5 runs. Baseline avg ‾16.99 ms, strict avg ‾61.11 ms, down from the previous ‾290.72 ms on the pre-patch release artifact. This strongly suggests the strict-mode startup regression was paying allocator signal/policy scaffolding on the host path. Awaiting the post-patch hardened measurement before deciding whether sigaction needs a separate fast path for bd-xxyb.¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-04-03T20:12:57Z¥"}, {¥"id¥": 1375, ¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-xxyb¥", ¥"author¥": ¥"LavenderMarsh¥", ¥"text¥": ¥"Second perf fix in progress: added a strict-mode fast path in signal_abi::sigaction so strict mode skips runtime_policy::decide/observe entirely and goes straight to validation + rt_sigaction marshalling, since strict mode never repairs signal installs. This targets the remaining Python startup tax after the allocator host-path reorder.¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-04-03T20:14:40Z¥"}, {¥"id¥": 1376, ¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-xxyb¥", ¥"author¥": ¥"LavenderMarsh¥", ¥"text¥": ¥"Fixed strict-mode Python startup regression in two steps. 1) host-thread pthread/TLS split in crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/pthread_abi.rs: host-created threads now use host pthread_self, pthread_key_{create,delete}, and pthread_{get,set}specific; fresh strict preload dropped gettid calls from ‾2252 to 2. 2) strict-mode raw fast paths for memcpy/strlen in crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/string_abi.rs so hot string ops skip runtime_policy::decide in strict mode; fresh local 5-run sample against /tmp/cargo-target/release/libfrankenlibc_abi.so improved strict startup from ‾58 ms to ‾37 ms. Current strict syscall profile: gettid=2, clock_gettime=142, futex=135. Verification via rch: cargo check -p frankenlibc-abi --tests passed; cargo check --workspace --all-targets passed; cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings passed; cargo fmt --check clean.¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-04-03T20:32:05Z¥"}, {¥"id¥": 1377, ¥"issue_id¥": ¥"bd-xxyb¥", ¥"author¥": ¥"LavenderMarsh¥", ¥"text¥": ¥"Closure evidence: rebuilt fresh release artifact via rch into /data/tmp/cargo-target/release/libfrankenlibc_abi.so, then ran the real smoke gate with an explicit pinned lib path after fixing scripts/ld_preload_smoke.sh to honor FRANKENLIBC_SMOKE_LIB_PATH. Command: rch exec -- env FRANKENLIBC_SMOKE_LIB_PATH=/data/tmp/cargo-target/release/libfrankenlibc_abi.so CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/data/tmp/cargo-target TIMEOUT_SECONDS=10 STRESS_ITERS=5 bash scripts/ld_preload_smoke.sh. Result: Summary passes=58 fails=0 skips=6, artifact bundle at target/ld_preload_smoke/20260404T002003Z. All strict and hardened Python cases passed, including python3_print and stress_python_{1..5}. This satisfies bd-xxyb acceptance criteria.¥", ¥"created_at¥": ¥"2026-04-04T00:21:07Z¥"}]}"
    },
